'''Lisandro Martínez''' (born 18 January 1998) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays primarily as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|ManchesU}} club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]]. Nicknamed "'''The Butcher'''", he is known for his aggressive style of play and accurate long passes from the back.<ref>{{cite news |title='If I have to step over dead bodies, I'll do it': Lisandro Martinez explains why he's nicknamed 'The Butcher' |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/manutd-2022-07-17-if-i-have-to-step-over-dead-bodies-ill-do-it-lisandro-martinez-explains-why-hes-nicknamed/ |date=18 July 2022}}</ref>

Martínez began his career at [[Newell's Old Boys]] before joining [[Defensa y Justicia]] in 2017, initially on loan. He signed for [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in 2019, where he made 120 appearances over three seasons and won two [[Eredivisie]] titles and one [[KNVB Cup]]. He won the [[List of AFC Ajax records and statistics#AFC Ajax prize winners|Ajax Player of the Year]] award in the 2021–22 season.

Martínez represented Argentina at [[Argentina national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Argentina national under-23 football team|under-23]] levels, before making his senior international debut in March 2019. He was a member of the Argentina squads that won the [[2021 Copa América]], the [[2022 Finalissima]], the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and the [[2024 Copa América]].

==Club career==
===Newell's Old Boys===
[[File:Lisandro Martínez treino 2016 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Martínez with [[Newell's Old Boys]] in 2016|255x255px]]

Born in [[Gualeguay, Entre Ríos|Gualeguay]], [[Entre Ríos Province]], Martínez had youth spells with Club Urquiza (Gualeguay, Entre Rios), Club Libertad (Gualeguay, Entre Rios) and [[Newell's Old Boys]].<ref name="Newell's">{{cite news |title=Lisandro Martínez: Los más chicos aprendemos de los referentes |url=http://www.newellsoldboys.com.ar/page/noticias_futbol/id/1151/title/Lisandro-Martinez-Los-mas-chicos-aprendemos-de-los-referentes |accessdate=14 February 2018 |publisher=Newell's Old Boys |date=13 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180214142203/http://www.newellsoldboys.com.ar/page/noticias_futbol/id/1151/title/Lisandro-Martinez-Los-mas-chicos-aprendemos-de-los-referentes|archive-date=14 February 2018}}</ref><ref name="Youth">{{cite news |title=Reconocieron a Lisandro Martínez por su desempeño en el fútbol nacional |url=http://eldiadegualeguay.com/p30263/ |accessdate=14 February 2018 |work=El Dia de Gualeguay |date=14 February 2017}}</ref> He made his professional debut for Newell's in the club's final fixture of the [[2016–17 Argentine Primera División|2016–17]] season, when he played the full match in a loss to [[Godoy Cruz Antonio Tomba|Godoy Cruz]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Newell's se despide del torneo y de varios referentes |url=https://redaccionrosario.com/2017/06/27/newells-se-despide-del-torneo-y-de-varios-referentes/ |website=redaccionrosario.com |date=27 June 2017|access-date=24 June 2022}}</ref><ref name="Soccerway profile">{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/lisandro-martinez/471671/ |title=Lisandro Martínez: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=2 February 2025}}</ref>

===Defensa y Justicia===
In August 2017, Martínez joined fellow [[Argentine Primera División]] side [[Defensa y Justicia]] on loan.<ref name="Joined Defensa">{{cite news |title=Lisandro Martínez, de Newell´s a Defensa |url=http://www.tycsports.com/futbol/lisandro-martinez-de-newells-defensa |accessdate=14 February 2018 |work=TyC Sports |date=11 August 2017}}</ref><ref name="BDFA profile">{{cite news |title=Lisandro Martínez profile |url=http://www.bdfa.com.ar/jugadores-LISANDRO-MARTINEZ-105493.html |accessdate=14 February 2018 |work=BDFA |date=14 February 2018}}</ref> His first appearance for Defensa arrived on 13 October in a defeat against [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]].<ref name="Soccerway profile" /> Two appearances later, he scored his first senior goal in an away win versus [[Club Atlético Temperley|Temperley]].<ref name="Soccerway profile" /><ref name="First goal">{{cite news |title=Defensa y Justicia aplastó a un Temperley que se hunde |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/futbol/temperley/temperley-defensa-justicia-superliga-horario-tv-formaciones_0_H1UUHF2CW.html |accessdate=14 February 2018 |work=Clarín |date=5 November 2017}}</ref> Defensa y Justicia purchased 50% of the rights to Martínez in June 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Newell's vende la mitad del pase de Lisandro Martínez a Defensa y Justicia |url=https://www.conclusion.com.ar/deportes/newells-vende-la-mitad-del-pase-de-lisandro-martinez-a-defensa-y-justicia/06/2018/ |website=conclusion.com.ar |date=4 June 2018|access-date=23 June 2022}}</ref>

===Ajax===
On 17 May 2019, Defensa y Justicia announced that a deal had been agreed with [[Eredivisie]] team [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]; subject to the passing of a medical.<ref name="Defensa y Justicia">{{cite news |title=Lisandro Martínez será transferido al Ajax de Holanda |url=http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/1114 |accessdate=17 May 2019 |work=Defensa y Justicia |date=17 May 2019 |archive-date=17 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417145905/http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/1114 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Ajax paid the Argentine side €7m for the transfer of Martínez.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Faisal |first=Hammad |date=29 June 2022 |title=Lisandro Martinez Analysis Can He Play in the Premier League? |url=https://crossbarhub.com/tactical-analysis/lisandro-martinez-analysis/ |access-date=18 July 2022 |website=CrossBar |archive-date=18 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220718101807/https://crossbarhub.com/tactical-analysis/lisandro-martinez-analysis/ |url-status=usurped }}</ref> Ajax announced the completion of the medical on 20 May, with the transfer to go through on 1 July.<ref name="Ajax">{{cite news |title=Ajax verzekert zich van komst Argentijn Lisandro Martínez |url=https://www.ajax.nl/streams/actueel/ajax-verzekert-zich-van-komst-argentijn-lisandro-martinez-.htm |accessdate=20 May 2019 |publisher=AFC Ajax |date=20 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521204623/https://www.ajax.nl/streams/actueel/ajax-verzekert-zich-van-komst-argentijn-lisandro-martinez-.htm|archive-date=21 May 2019}}</ref> He penned a four-year contract, with the option of a further year.<ref name="Ajax"/> He didn't officially join until July, though did feature in June friendlies with [[Quick '20]] and [[AaB Fodbold|AaB]].<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> Before Ajax signed him, they tracked his progress for two and a half years.<ref name="AjaxScoutReport">{{cite web |title=The first time we saw Martínez |url=https://english.ajax.nl/articles/the-first-time-we-saw-martinez/ |website=english.ajax.nl |date=27 July 2022 |access-date=28 July 2022}}</ref> His competitive bow came in the [[2019 Johan Cruyff Shield]] against [[PSV Eindhoven]], as Ajax won the trophy following a two-goal victory.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> He was voted [[Player of the match|man of the match]] in his second Eredivisie game, a win over [[FC Emmen|Emmen]].<ref name="AS1">{{cite news |title=NB: 'Waarom zou je Tadic niet als eerste spits zien?' |url=http://www.ajaxshowtime.com/index.php/article/bijzaken-en-geruchten/124718/nb-waarom-zou-je-tadic-niet-als-eerste-spits-zien |accessdate=10 August 2019 |work=Ajax Showtime |date=10 August 2019}}</ref>

Martínez netted his first Ajax goal on 28 September, as he opened the scoring in a 2–0 victory over [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] at the [[Johan Cruyff Arena]].<ref name="TYC1">{{cite news |title=Ajax venció a Groningen y sigue como líder de la Eredivisie |url=https://www.tycsports.com/futbol-internacional/ajax-vencio-a-groningen-y-sigue-como-lider-de-la-eredivisie-20190928.html |accessdate=28 September 2019 |work=TyC Sports |date=28 September 2019}}</ref> He scored again against [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] in November, in a campaign which was ended prematurely due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref name="Soccerway profile" /> In his first match of [[2020–21 AFC Ajax season|2020–21]], Martínez got his third Ajax goal in a home win versus [[RKC Waalwijk]] on 20 September.<ref name="Soccerway profile" />

===Manchester United===
On 16 July 2022, it was announced that [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] had agreed a deal with Ajax for the signing of Martínez for a reported transfer fee between £47&nbsp;million to £49&nbsp;million, plus £8.5&nbsp;million in add-ons.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lisandro Martinez: Man Utd agree to sign Argentina centre-back from Ajax in £57m deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62170735 |website=BBC Sport |date=17 July 2022 |accessdate=27 July 2022}}</ref> The transfer was officially completed on 27 July, when Martínez signed a five-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Martinez signs for United |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/lisandro-martinez-completes-signing-for-man-united |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=27 July 2022 |access-date=27 July 2022}}</ref> The next day, it was confirmed that he would wear the number six shirt last worn by [[Paul Pogba]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Revealed: Martinez's squad number |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/lisandro-martinez-man-utd-kit-number-revealed-ahead-of-2022-23-season |date=28 July 2022|access-date=28 July 2022 |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |first=Mikey |last=Partington}}</ref> On 7 August, Martínez made his club debut in a 2–1 home loss against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Manchester United 1–2 Brighton: Erik ten Hag suffers defeat in first Premier League game |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62366387 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2022 |access-date=7 August 2022}}</ref> However, after performances against [[Liverpool F.C.–Manchester United F.C. rivalry|rivals]] [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], he received the Manchester United Player of the Month award for August.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hill|first=Courtney|title=Lisandro Martinez wins Man Utd Player of the Month award for August 2022|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/lisandro-martinez-wins-man-utd-player-of-the-month-award-for-august-2022|date=1 September 2022|access-date=28 May 2024|publisher=Manchester United F.C.}}</ref>

On 22 January 2023, Martínez scored his first goal for Manchester United in a 3–2 defeat against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] at the [[Emirates Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Morgan |first=Richard |title=Martinez scores first goal for Manchester United in a 3–2 defeat against Arsenal at the Emirates |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/arsenal-vs-man-utd/report/464835 |work=Sky Sports |date=23 January 2023 }}</ref> His first trophy with the club came on 26 February, with a win over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in the [[2023 EFL Cup final]].<ref name="LC23"/> On 13 April, Martínez injured his right foot while playing in the first leg of the Europa League quarter-final against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]]. The following day, it was confirmed that he fractured the fifth metatarsal bone in his right foot and would miss the remainder of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lisandro Martinez: Manchester United defender to miss rest of season with fractured foot {{!}} Raphael Varane out 'for a few weeks' |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12857379/lisandro-martinez-manchester-united-defender-to-miss-rest-of-season-with-fractured-foot |access-date=23 April 2023 |website=Sky Sports }}</ref>

On 29 September, Martínez reinjured his foot,<ref>{{cite web |title=Man Utd injury update on Lisandro Martinez |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/injury-update-on-lisandro-martinez-before-crystal-palace-game-29-september |date=29 September 2023 |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |access-date=5 February 2024}}</ref> and was sidelined for four months, returning on 14 January 2024 as a substitute in Manchester United's 2–2 draw against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Manchester United vs. Tottenham Hotspur 2 – 2 |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2024/01/14/england/premier-league/manchester-united-fc/tottenham-hotspur-football-club/4082223/ |website=Soccerway |date=14 January 2024 |access-date=5 February 2024}}</ref> On 4 February, in a match against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], he was substituted in the 71st minute after a collision with West Ham defender [[Vladimír Coufal]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Sam|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5250083/2024/02/04/man-united-martinez-injury/|title=Lisandro Martinez's knee injury a 'personal disaster' – Manchester United boss Erik ten Hag|date=5 February 2024|access-date=28 May 2024|website=The Athletic}}</ref> It was then confirmed that he had sustained an [[Medial collateral ligament|MCL]] injury, and was expected to be out for at least eight weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Martinez injury confirmed|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/lisandro-martinez-injury-confirmed-by-man-utd-after-withdrawal-in-west-ham-game|publisher=Manchester United F.C.|date=6 February 2024|access-date=28 May 2024}}</ref> He returned on 25 May in the [[2024 FA Cup final]] against [[Manchester derby|local rivals]] [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], where United triumphed with a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite news|last=Yew|first=Oliver|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/man-city-vs-man-utd/report/504674|title=Man City 1–2 Man Utd: Erik ten Hag's side end season on high with stunning FA Cup final win at Wembley|date=26 May 2024|access-date=26 May 2024|website=Sky Sports}}</ref>

On 5 January 2025, Martínez scored the opening goal in a 2–2 draw against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at [[Anfield]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=5 January 2025 |title=Report: Liverpool 2 United 2 |url= https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/match-report-from-liverpool-v-man-utd-in-premier-league-on-5-january-2024 |access-date=11 January 2025 |publisher=[[Manchester United F.C.]]}}</ref> He became the first Manchester United player to score at their [[Liverpool F.C.–Manchester United F.C. rivalry|rivals]]' ground since [[Jesse Lingard]] in 2018, ending a drought of five league visits to Anfield without a goal.<ref>{{Cite web|date=5 January 2025 |title=Report: Liverpool 2–2 Man Utd: Key stats |url= https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cp83g05zg0yo |access-date=11 January 2025 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 26 January, Martínez's deflected shot handed United a 1–0 victory over [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] at [[Craven Cottage]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/704503|title=Lisandro Martínez goal gives stale Man United win at Fulham|date=27 January 2025|publisher=[[ESPN]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127092659/https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/704503|archive-date=27 January 2025|url-status=live|access-date=28 January 2025}}</ref> A week later, on 2 February, he sustained an [[Anterior cruciate ligament|ACL]] injury during a match against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], which would sideline him for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/revealed-journalist-reveals-details-of-lisandro-martinezs-injury-he-is-out-for-the-season-40658359 |title=Revealed: Journalist reveals details of Lisandro Martinez's injury, he is out for the season |publisher=OneFootball |date=3 February 2025 }}</ref>

On 13 April 2026, Martinez received a straight red card for pulling the hair of [[Dominic Calvert-Lewin]] in their 2-1 home defeat to [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and was suspended for three games.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Stone |first=Simon |date=5 December 2024 |title=Leeds' first win at Old Trafford against 10 man Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c2lwv150jwwt |access-date=15 April 2026 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

==International career==
Martínez won four caps for the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina under-20 team]] at the [[2017 South American Youth Football Championship]] in Ecuador.<ref name="Soccerway profile" /><ref name="Youth" /><ref name="U20s 1">{{cite news |title=Se terminó el año para los juveniles |url=http://www.afa.com.ar/6363/lista-para-la-semana-que-viene |accessdate=14 February 2018 |publisher=Argentine Football Association |date=29 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308080850/http://www.afa.com.ar/6363/lista-para-la-semana-que-viene|archive-date=8 March 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> The first came during the first stage against [[Venezuela national under-20 football team|Venezuela]], while the other three arrived during the final stage as Argentina finished fourth place and subsequently qualified for the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in South Korea.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> He received a call-up for the U-20 World Cup but failed to make an appearance, appearing on the substitutes bench once against [[Guinea national under-20 football team|Guinea]].<ref name="Soccerway profile"/><ref name="U20s 2">{{cite news |title=Argentina Sub 20 regresa a los trabajos en Ezeiza con miras al mundial de la categoría |url=http://conmebol.com/es/argentina-sub-20-regresa-los-trabajos-en-ezeiza-con-miras-al-mundial-de-la-categoria|publisher=CONMEBOL|date=27 March 2017|access-date=14 February 2018|language=es}}</ref> Martínez made one appearance for Argentina at [[Argentina national under-23 football team|under-23 level]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=Lisandro Martínez |url=https://www.besoccer.com/player/lisandro-martinez-357579 |website=besoccer.com|access-date=23 June 2022}}</ref>{{Better source needed|reason=Independent secondary source|date=May 2024}} in a 5–0 friendly victory against Bolivia in September 2019.<ref name="AFA2">{{cite news|title=La Selección Sub 23 jugará ante Bolivia desde las 19, en el estadio de Banfield |url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/la-seleccion-sub-23-enfrentara-a-bolivia-desde-las-19-en-el-estadio-de-banfield|publisher=Argentine Football Association|date=3 September 2019|access-date=4 September 2019|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Argentina U-23 5–0 Bolivia U-23|url=https://www.besoccer.com/match/argentina-sub-23/bolivia-sub-23/2019596145|website=Besoccer|access-date=23 June 2022}}</ref>{{Better source needed|reason=Independent secondary source|date=May 2024}}

[[File:Argentina - Colombia 2022 (51).jpg|thumb|right|Martínez with Argentina in 2022]]

In March 2019, Martínez received his first call-up to the [[Argentina national football team|senior team]].<ref name="AFA1">{{cite news |title=Hay que trabajar para el futuro de la Selección |url=http://www.afa.com.ar/11551/hay-que-trabajar-para-el-futuro-de-la-seleccion|publisher=Argentine Football Association|date=7 March 2019|language=es|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327172431/http://www.afa.com.ar/11551/hay-que-trabajar-para-el-futuro-de-la-seleccion|archive-date=27 March 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> He debuted against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] on 22 March in [[Madrid]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=El elogio de Lisandro Martínez a Lionel Messi: "Es un líder nato"|url=https://www.tycsports.com/seleccion-argentina/seleccion-argentina-lisandro-martinez-elogio-lionel-messi-id330682.html|website=[[TyC Sports]]|date=27 March 2021|language=es}}</ref> Martínez made one appearance at the [[2021 Copa América]],<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> which Argentina won.<ref name="ca2021">{{Cite news|title=Argentina 1–0 Brazil|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57776158|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=11 July 2021|access-date=23 June 2022}}</ref> He was an unused substitute in Argentina's 3–0 victory over [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in the [[2022 Finalissima]].<ref name="finalissima">{{Cite news|title=Italy 0–3 Argentina: Messi and Di Maria shine in impressive Finalissima win|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61653337|website=BBC Sport|date=1 June 2022|access-date=2 June 2022}}</ref> At the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], Martinez came off the bench against [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] in the round of 16, making an important block on a shot by [[Aziz Behich]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Martinez plays his part as Argentina progress|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/lisandro-martinez-helps-argentina-advance-to-2022-world-cup-qfs-with-win-v-australia|website=Manchester United|access-date=1 March 2023}}</ref> Martinez was part of the starting XI against [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in the quarter-finals and came off the bench against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in the semis.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2022 FIFA World Cup|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/netherlands-vs-argentina/teams/463021|website=[[Sky Sports]]|date=1 March 2023}}</ref> In the final against title-holders [[France national football team|France]], he was an unused substitute as Argentina won 4–2 on penalties to win their third World Cup title.<ref name="FWC22">{{Cite news|first=Phil|last=McNulty|title=World Cup final: Argentina beat France on penalties in dramatic Qatar showpiece|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63932622|website=BBC Sport|date=18 December 2022}}</ref>

On 15 June 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/nomina-de-futbolistas-convocados-para-disputar-la-copa-america-2026-en-estados-unidos|title=Nómina de futbolistas convocados por Lionel Scaloni para disputar la Copa América 2024 en Estados Unidos|trans-title=List of footballers called by Lionel Scaloni to compete in the 2024 Copa América in the United States|publisher=[[Argentine Football Association]]|date=15 June 2024|language=es}}</ref> He scored his first international goal, putting his team ahead in a 1–1 draw against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] in the quarter-finals of the tournament, which ended with a victory in the penalty shootout.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://copaamerica.com/en/news/lisandro-martinez-scores-first-international-goal |title=Lisandro Martinez Finds Perfect Time To Score First International Goal At CONMEBOL Copa América™ |publisher=Copa América |date=5 July 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/video-lisandro-martinez-scores-first-054800468.html |title=Video: Lisandro Martinez scores his first goal for Argentina in Copa America quarter-final |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=5 July 2024 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
He is primarily a [[centre-back]], though he is capable of playing at [[left-back]] and as a [[Defensive Midfielder|defensive-midfielder]], having played there at times for Defensa y Justicia and Ajax.<ref name="CLA1">{{cite news |title=Lisandro Martínez, de la infancia humilde en Gualeguay al lujo del Ajax goleador: "Estaría bueno que los futbolistas ayudemos más a los que lo necesitan" |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/lisandro-martinez-infancia-humilde-gualeguay-lujo-ajax-goleador-bueno-futbolistas-ayudemos-necesitan-_0_y8SOo0PBl.html |accessdate=27 December 2020 |work=Clarín |date=26 October 2020}}</ref><ref name="TG1">{{cite news |title=Ten exciting Champions League debutants to watch this week |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/who-scored-blog/2019/sep/17/champions-league-debuts-exciting-this-week|access-date=18 September 2019 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=17 September 2019}}</ref> He is a ball-playing centre-back and is known for his range of passing and composure on the ball.<ref>{{cite news |title=Transfer window: 10 bargain signings of the summer so far |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/who-scored-blog/2019/jul/03/transfer-window-bargain-deals-summer |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=3 July 2019|access-date=8 July 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Ronaldo's bombshell shows how far Man Utd have fallen. It might be just what they need |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/premier-league/teams/manchester-united/epl-2022-cristiano-ronaldo-transfer-news-manchester-united-erik-ten-hag-chelsea-premier-league-latest-update/news-story/d78c653e261c296e400c36b7a1402b65 |website=foxsports.com.au |date=6 July 2022|access-date=8 July 2022}}</ref> In the 2021–22 Eredivisie season, he averaged more passes per 90 minutes than any other player.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lisandro Martinez: Man Utd and Arsenal transfer target has shone for Ajax and offers brains, brawn and versatility |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12646170/lisandro-martinez-man-utd-and-arsenal-transfer-target-has-shone-for-ajax-and-offers-brains-brawn-and-versatility |website=Sky Sports |date=13 July 2022|access-date=13 July 2022}}</ref> Before signing him, Ajax's scouts characterised Martínez as a left-footed ball-playing defender who is "tough as nails" and possesses winning mentality.<ref name="AjaxScoutReport"/> At Manchester United, his performances earned him comparisons to legendary former United defender [[Nemanja Vidić]], with Vidic himself praising Martínez for his aggressive defending and leadership.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Murphy |first=Daniel |date=8 January 2023 |title=How Lisandro Martinez can solidify comparison to Manchester United legend |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-lisandro-martinez-vidic-25907982 |access-date=1 March 2023 |website=Manchester Evening News }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Victor |first=Tom |date=10 February 2023 |title=Man Utd legend Vidic gives verdict on Martinez after Ferdinand claim |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/vidic-ferdinand-lisandro-martinez-comments-29188629 |access-date=1 March 2023 |website=The Mirror }}</ref> Despite his relatively short stature for a defender, standing at 5'9", he is also effective in duels.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/12675315/is-lisandro-martinezs-height-really-a-problem |title=Lisandro Martinez at Manchester United: Is 5'9" height a problem for Argentina defender in the Premier League? |work=Sky Sports |last1=Bate |first1=Adam |date=22 August 2022 |access-date=9 July 2024 }}</ref>

